{{R|Golden Compass||2}} is an {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Ancient|Ancient|2}} {{2|Relics|Relic}} offered by {{KW|Tezcatara||2}} at the start of {{2|Acts#Act 2|Act 2}}. It replaces the Act 2 map with a single path that is 2 floors longer than the regular Act 2 and always has the following {{2|Map Locations}} in order:
* {{2|Map Locations#Monsters|Monster}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Unknown|Unknown}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Monsters|Monster}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Rest Sites|Rest Site}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Monsters|Monster}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Rest Sites|Rest Site}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Unknown|Unknown}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Treasure Room|Treasure Room}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Unknown|Unknown}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Treasure Room|Treasure Room}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Unknown|Unknown}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Merchant|Merchant}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Elites|Elite}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Rest Sites|Rest Site}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Elites|Elite}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Rest Sites|Rest Site}}
* {{2|Map Locations#Boss|Boss Encounter}}

== Obtaining Golden Compass ==
Can be offered at the start of [[StS2:Acts#Act 2|Act 2]] by {{KW|Tezcatara||2}}.

===Spawn Restrictions===
*Because '''Golden Compass''' shares a relic pool with {{R|Pumpkin Candle||2}} and {{R|Toy Box||2}}, only 1 of the 3 can be offered by {{KW|Tezcatara||2}}.

==Notes==
* {{2|Map Locations#Unknown|Unknown Locations}} on this Map will ''always'' lead to [[Slay the Spire 2:Events|Events]], rather than {{2|Map Locations#Monsters|Monsters}}, {{2|Map Locations#Treasure Room|Treasure Rooms}}, and {{2|Map Locations#Merchant|Merchants}}.
*This Map provides ''2 additional'' [[Slay the Spire 2:Map Locations|Map Locations]] between the [[Slay the Spire 2:Ancients|Ancient]] and [[Slay the Spire 2:Bosses|Boss]].

== Trivia ==
The name of this relic might be a reference to the 1995 novel [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northern_Lights_(Pullman_novel) The Golden Compass].

